  "review_sentences": [
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 0,
      "text": "The paper presents a an interesting novel approach to train neural networks with so called peer regularization which aims to provide robustness to adversarial attacks.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 1,
      "text": "The idea is to add a graph neural network to a spatial CNN.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 2,
      "text": "A graph is defined over similar training samples which are found using a Monte Carlo approximation.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 3,
      "text": "The regularization using graphs reminds me of recent work at ICML on semi-supervised learning (Kamnitsas et al. (2018) Semi-supervised learning via compact latent space clustering) which is using a graph to approximate cluster density which acts as a regularizer for training on labelled data.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_other",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 4,
      "text": "The main problem I see with these approaches is that they rely on sufficiently large batch sizes which could be (currently) problematic for many real-world applications.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_replicability",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 5,
      "text": "Memory and computation limitations are mentioned, but not sufficently discussed.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 6,
      "text": "It would be good to add further details on practical limitations.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_request",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-request_edit",
      "aspect": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 7,
      "text": "Experiments are limited to benchmark data using MNIST, CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_quote",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 8,
      "text": "Comprehensive evaluation has been carried out with insightful experiments and good comparison to state-of-the-art.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_substance",
      "polarity": "pol_positive"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 9,
      "text": "Both white- and black-box adversarial attacks are explored with promising results for the proposed approach.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_substance",
      "polarity": "pol_positive"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 10,
      "text": "However, it is difficult to draw conclusions for real-world problems of larger scale.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "arg_other",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 11,
      "text": "The authors state that proposed framework can be added to any baseline model, but miss to clearly mention the limitations.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 12,
      "text": "It is stated that future work will aim at scaling PeerNets to benchmarks like ImageNet, but it is unclear how this could be done.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HkgMKRcth7",
      "sentence_index": 13,
      "text": "Is there any hope this could be applied to problems like 3D imaging data or videos?",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_request",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-request_explanation",
      "aspect": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "polarity": "none"
    }
